    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Period and culture of the Korean dynasty that ruled the Korean peninsula from 1392 to 1910, founded by Yi Sŏng-gye, posthumously known as King T’aejo (reiged 1392-1398). It is characterized by the establishment of Neo-Confucianism as the official ideology, encouragement of a modest and practical lifestyle, and abandonment of patronage for more extravagant art.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
